   {:e #blake3 "5a4fd5eb91dc3a684210959335f227398f4d626440e5abb81037ae8eabdb1d46" :a :task/description :v "CONTEXT: Current steering produces generic templates ('what connects X to Y?'). The system has geometric knowledge in concept centroids (256-dim vectors) that it cannot articulate. The discrepancy between observation and centroid encodes WHAT WAS NEW.\n\nAPPROACH: Add to concept.rs:\n\npub fn compute_discrepancy_brief(\n    store: &Store,\n    observation_embedding: &[f32],\n    concept_entity: EntityId,\n    surprise: f32,\n) -> Option<String> {\n    // 1. Get concept centroid embedding\n    let centroid = get_concept_embedding(store, concept_entity)?;\n    \n    // 2. Compute discrepancy vector: what's new = observation - centroid\n    let discrepancy: Vec<f32> = observation_embedding.iter()\n        .zip(centroid.iter())\n        .map(|(o, c)| o - c)\n        .collect();\n    \n    // 3. Find stored observation closest to discrepancy vector\n    //    This observation represents 'what was novel about the new observation'\n    let novel_obs = find_nearest_observation(store, &discrepancy)?;\n    \n    // 4. Find stored observation closest to centroid\n    //    This observation represents 'what the concept expected'\n    let expected_obs = find_nearest_observation(store, &centroid)?;\n    \n    // 5. Keyword set difference\n    let novel_words = tokenize(&novel_obs.body);\n    let expected_words = tokenize(&expected_obs.body);\n    let new_keywords: Vec<&str> = novel_words.iter()\n        .filter(|w| !expected_words.contains(w) && w.len() > 4)\n        .take(5).collect();\n    let expected_keywords: Vec<&str> = expected_words.iter()\n        .filter(|w| !novel_words.contains(w) && w.len() > 4)\n        .take(5).collect();\n    \n    // 6. Articulate\n    if new_keywords.is_empty() { return None; }\n    let concept_name = concept_name_from_entity(store, concept_entity);\n    Some(format!(\n        '{concept_name} expected: {{{expected}}}. You found: {{{novel}}}.',\n        expected = expected_keywords.join(', '),\n        novel = new_keywords.join(', ')\n    ))\n}\n\nAlso needs find_nearest_observation(store, embedding) -> Option<ObsRef> that scans :exploration/embedding datoms and returns the observation body. Same pattern as find_nearest_concept but for observations.\n\nWire into observe.rs: call compute_discrepancy_brief when surprise > 0.3 and include the result in responsive_parts.\n\nACCEPTANCE: (A) For a surprising observation, the output shows expected vs found keywords. (B) For a confirming observation (surprise < 0.3), no discrepancy brief. (C) Keywords are content words (>4 chars), not function words. (D) All existing tests pass.\n\nFILE: crates/braid-kernel/src/concept.rs + crates/braid/src/commands/observe.rs" :op :assert}
